title: South Shore Park rock revetment, Milwaukee
description:
The rock revetment along the shore of Lake Michigan at South Shore Park in Milwaukee, Wisconsin.
The revetment provides shoreline erosion protection. A rock groin (built perpendicular to the shoreline) is seen in the distance.
South Shore Park also has an offshore rock breakwater, to provide further coastal protection for a marina and beach. 

Plants are colonizing the upper margin of the rock revetment. The more common plants found in and along the revetment include common milkweed (Asclepias syriaca), riverbank grape (vitis riparia), white sweet clover (Melilotus alba), green ash (Fraxinus pennsylvanica), evening primrose (Oenothera biennis), black walnut (Juglans nigra) and sandbar willow (Salix interior).

Photo taken early August 2023. Original key: IMG_5983
